90

E. Display Controls
unsci_display_level (List: Full, Summary Only, Hidden to Public) —
reviewers/editors always see full.
F. Integrity (auto)
unsci_lastcheck (Calendar — updated on each save)
unsci_complete (Checkbox — indicates minimally valid record)
5) Validation Rules
When unsci_active=Yes : - At least one unsci_entries item with scope and reason .
- If unsci_resolved=Yes → unsci_resolution_notes required; set resolver and
timestamp.
- On pass: set unsci_complete=1 and update unsci_lastcheck .
- On fail: block Publish transition (configurable).
Optional behaviors (params): - Auto‑tag Article with un-scientific when active;
remove when fully resolved.
- Auto‑notify authors when flagged or when resolution requested.
6) Rendering (Front‑end)
Badge (after title): Un Scientific with color based on risk_level max;
hover shows count of entries & status (Resolved/Unresolved).
Panel (after content): 
Table/list of entries with: Scope, Reasons, Notes, Requested Action,
CreatedBy/At.
If unsci_resolved=Yes : show Resolution notes & resolver/time.
If unsci_related_ai=Yes : add a “See AI Usage” quick link.
Respect unsci_display_level (public vs reviewer/editor).
Use WebAsset API for minimal CSS/JS (accordion, status chips).
